Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a light-brown pottery wine-jar, the fabric is black in section and contains a number of small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and very faint traces of one line of black-painted hieratic text, very obscured by a dark-brown granular deposit.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393461) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393461)
